WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.923 --> 00:00:09.801
{\an8}<i>[foreboding music]</i>

2
00:00:09.884 --> 00:00:14.014
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

3
00:00:14.097 --> 00:00:16.475
{\an8}And now you're saying you
know the man from the marathon?

4
00:00:16.558 --> 00:00:18.644
{\an8}I was his foster mother
for a little over a year.

5
00:00:18.727 --> 00:00:21.396
{\an8}Last I heard. he was arrested
for selling OxyContin.

6
00:00:21.479 --> 00:00:24.107
{\an8}Not a single visitor until
a week before his release.

7
00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:26.026
Visitor was Caroline Finch.

8
00:00:26.109 --> 00:00:28.070
Kyle Smit is now a suspect.

9
00:00:28.153 --> 00:00:29.321
<i>You think he could be violent?</i>

10
00:00:29.404 --> 00:00:30.489
<i>I think even good people can do</i>

11
00:00:30.572 --> 00:00:31.823
<i>bad things if they're pushed.</i>

12
00:00:31.906 --> 00:00:32.908
You had a gambling problem.

13
00:00:32.991 --> 00:00:33.909
I went into business with you.

14
00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:34.910
You're so grateful.

15
00:00:34.993 --> 00:00:35.994
I am grateful.

16
00:00:36.077 --> 00:00:37.079
Thanks. buddy.

17
00:00:37.162 --> 00:00:38.997
<i>Brian was not born disabled.</i>

18
00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:40.290
<i>There was an accident.</i>

19
00:00:40.373 --> 00:00:41.792
And it was Lia's fault.

20
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.669
<i>Lia has grown up with
that on her conscience.</i>

21
00:00:43.752 --> 00:00:45.045
Ready?

22
00:00:45.128 --> 00:00:46.630
<i>-And it's shaped who she is...</i>
-Bitch!

23
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.090
<i>As a person.</i>

24
00:00:48.173 --> 00:00:49.174
I need you to do
stupid shit so that I

25
00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:50.842
can smooth everything over.

26
00:00:50.925 --> 00:00:52.678
<i>But I need you to feel
nauseous from the pain meds</i>

27
00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:54.680
<i>so I can keep my mind busy
thinking of what might help.</i>

28
00:00:54.763 --> 00:00:57.182
<i>Carrie has to hide
because she's famous.</i>

29
00:00:57.265 --> 00:00:59.685
<i>You can't have two
famous people. Milo.</i>

30
00:00:59.768 --> 00:01:01.561
That would be a problem.

31
00:01:01.644 --> 00:01:03.397
<i>-Yeah. she was all done up.</i>
-Hi. I'm Maryanne.

32
00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:04.606
Is this your place?

33
00:01:04.689 --> 00:01:05.689
Yeah.

34
00:01:07.275 --> 00:01:08.401
We found a body.

35
00:01:14.991 --> 00:01:18.328
<i>[gentle music]</i>

36
00:01:18.411 --> 00:01:21.373
<i>So. here's where things
stand with the case.</i>

37
00:01:21.456 --> 00:01:23.292
<i>Carrie Finch
and Kyle Smit rented</i>

38
00:01:23.375 --> 00:01:25.294
<i>a lake house in North Dunes.</i>

39
00:01:25.377 --> 00:01:27.879
<i>And it appears that
Milo was with them.</i>

40
00:01:27.962 --> 00:01:30.716
The rental's now empty.

41
00:01:30.799 --> 00:01:32.718
We're still doing
a forensic search.

42
00:01:32.801 --> 00:01:36.221
And the vehicle that they were
using was left near the scene.

43
00:01:36.304 --> 00:01:37.931
In the rental. there
was evidence that Milo

44
00:01:38.014 --> 00:01:39.391
was being well cared for...

45
00:01:39.474 --> 00:01:42.144
age-appropriate food.
changes of clothing.

46
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:45.939
But we also found
the body of an adult male

47
00:01:46.022 --> 00:01:49.526
in the lake adjacent
to the rental property.

48
00:01:49.609 --> 00:01:51.403
We haven't done a
formal identification.

49
00:01:51.486 --> 00:01:53.155
but it appears to be Kyle Smit.

50
00:01:53.238 --> 00:01:55.032
-Oh. my god.
-Wait. so...

51
00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:56.408
Oh. my god.

52
00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:58.744
So. now it's just
Carrie who has Milo?

53
00:01:58.827 --> 00:02:00.162
We don't know for sure.

54
00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:01.163
Do you know what
car they're in now?

55
00:02:01.246 --> 00:02:02.456
No. I'm afraid not.

56
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:04.166
OK. so you don't know anything?

57
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:05.083
Yeah. actually. we
have less information

58
00:02:05.166 --> 00:02:06.877
now than we did before.

59
00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:08.879
At least before you knew what
kind of car to look for...

60
00:02:08.962 --> 00:02:11.882
How did Kyle Smit die?

61
00:02:11.965 --> 00:02:14.968
It appears to be a gunshot
wound to the back of the head.

62
00:02:15.051 --> 00:02:16.261
Holy fuck.

63
00:02:16.344 --> 00:02:18.430
So. Carrie's got a gun then. right?

64
00:02:18.513 --> 00:02:20.349
'Cause that's new information.

65
00:02:20.432 --> 00:02:23.060
Like. that's definitely
brand-new information.

66
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:26.771
So she... well.
she executed him?

67
00:02:31.526 --> 00:02:36.698
I found an item in the
rental. and I recognized.

68
00:02:36.781 --> 00:02:37.782
Is this Milo's?

69
00:02:40.201 --> 00:02:42.454
Uh. that's... that's Mr. Chips.

70
00:02:42.537 --> 00:02:45.707
Oh. my god. Mr. Chips.

71
00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:47.709
Was it with him when
he went to school?

72
00:02:47.792 --> 00:02:48.710
Uh.

73
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:50.212
Was it in his backpack. maybe?

74
00:02:50.295 --> 00:02:52.130
No.

75
00:02:52.213 --> 00:02:53.757
Carrie got ahold of it somehow.

76
00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:57.594
Either she took it.
or someone gave it to her.

77
00:02:57.677 --> 00:03:00.973
Can any of you tell me when's
the last time you saw this?

78
00:03:01.056 --> 00:03:03.392
Easter weekend.

79
00:03:03.475 --> 00:03:06.812
But Easter was before you
hired the nanny. correct?

80
00:03:06.895 --> 00:03:07.854
Yes.

81
00:03:07.937 --> 00:03:09.273
Yeah. that's right.

82
00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:10.774
I mean. that's before
we'd even met Ana.

83
00:03:10.857 --> 00:03:13.193
If Carrie got hold of
Mr. Chips that Easter.

84
00:03:13.276 --> 00:03:15.862
then that changes everything.

85
00:03:15.945 --> 00:03:18.865
It means that Carrie was... was
interested in Milo before she

86
00:03:18.948 --> 00:03:21.493
started working with
Jenny Kaminski. which

87
00:03:21.576 --> 00:03:27.124
means that she met
Milo some other way.

88
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:28.584
through someone else.

89
00:03:28.667 --> 00:03:29.918
OK.

90
00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:31.336
Can... can you walk me
through that weekend?

91
00:03:31.419 --> 00:03:33.380
Yeah. it was a last-minute trip.

92
00:03:33.463 --> 00:03:35.716
Uh. it was a getaway to
a ranch a couple of hours

93
00:03:35.799 --> 00:03:37.217
south of here.

94
00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:39.386
We got there Friday night.

95
00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:42.723
Mr. Chips goes missing
Saturday afternoon.

96
00:03:42.806 --> 00:03:45.976
I mean. Milo just cried his
eyes out. he was distraught.

97
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:48.145
We searched for hours.

98
00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:52.024
And you're 100% sure Milo
brought him to the ranch?

99
00:03:52.107 --> 00:03:53.066
Yeah.

100
00:03:53.149 --> 00:03:54.776
I helped Milo unpack his bag.

101
00:03:54.859 --> 00:03:57.988
I remember tucking
Mr. Chips into Milo's bed

102
00:03:58.071 --> 00:04:00.073
on Friday night.

103
00:04:00.156 --> 00:04:02.075
Can we pinpoint a time?

104
00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:04.036
Was he there in the morning?

105
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:05.286
There.

106
00:04:07.789 --> 00:04:09.541
OK. so he was there
Saturday morning?

107
00:04:09.624 --> 00:04:10.834
-Yeah.
-OK.

108
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:12.461
Can you talk me
through the afternoon?

109
00:04:12.544 --> 00:04:14.004
Did you go into town?

110
00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:15.380
Go grocery shopping?

111
00:04:15.463 --> 00:04:17.299
Milo could have
forgotten him at a store.

112
00:04:17.382 --> 00:04:20.218
We had groceries delivered.

113
00:04:20.301 --> 00:04:21.219
Maybe the delivery person...

114
00:04:21.302 --> 00:04:23.055
No. no. you don't...

115
00:04:23.138 --> 00:04:25.724
the groceries were already at
the house when we got there.

116
00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:29.436
Oh. I went into
town later for juice.

117
00:04:29.519 --> 00:04:32.230
Uh. they screwed up
the order. so there

118
00:04:32.313 --> 00:04:33.941
just... there wasn't enough.

119
00:04:34.024 --> 00:04:36.526
But that was hours after
Mr. Chips had disappeared

120
00:04:36.609 --> 00:04:37.694
and we'd been searching. so.

121
00:04:37.777 --> 00:04:38.570
OK.

122
00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:40.030
What about maid service?

123
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:41.198
Or repairs of the ranch?

124
00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:42.199
Things like that?

125
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.742
Um. no.

126
00:04:43.825 --> 00:04:45.202
How could Carrie have
gotten a hold of Mr. Chips?

127
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.621
It... it doesn't make any sense.

128
00:04:47.704 --> 00:04:50.707
Someone had to have
given him to Carrie.

129
00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:54.253
Maybe by accident.
maybe on purpose.

130
00:04:54.336 --> 00:04:55.879
Oh. that just seems so extreme.

131
00:04:55.962 --> 00:04:57.381
Well. what other
explanation is there?

132
00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:58.465
I don't know.

133
00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:00.217
But there has to be something.

134
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.636
I'm gonna need the name of
everyone who was at the ranch.

135
00:05:02.719 --> 00:05:04.346
Any friend that
visited that weekend

136
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:06.014
could have a connection
to Carrie Finch.

137
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:07.474
You don't understand.

138
00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:10.060
There was no one else
that visited the ranch.

139
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:11.603
It was just the five of us.

140
00:05:19.527 --> 00:05:21.947
It was just the
people in this room.

141
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:25.742
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

142
00:05:34.751 --> 00:05:36.336
Do you think the
detective will come back?

143
00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:37.629
Yeah. of course
he's gonna come back.

144
00:05:37.712 --> 00:05:38.964
He thinks one of
us knows Carrie.

145
00:05:39.047 --> 00:05:40.090
But that's insane.

146
00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:41.258
He doesn't know that.

147
00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:43.051
No one here knows Carrie.

148
00:05:43.134 --> 00:05:45.262
Then how did she
get Mr. Chips. huh?

149
00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:47.514
There has to be a logical
explanation. but I just...

150
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:48.932
I don't see it.
It doesn't make sense.

151
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:51.351
Then let's make
it make sense. yeah?

152
00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:52.811
Let's talk it through.

153
00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:54.605
If no one here gave
Mr. Chips to Carrie.

154
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:56.356
then she got him some other way.

155
00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:57.983
How?

156
00:05:58.066 --> 00:06:00.110
There... there is an alarm
at the ranch house. right?

157
00:06:00.193 --> 00:06:01.361
There was. I remember.

158
00:06:01.444 --> 00:06:02.696
Yeah. I set it that night.

159
00:06:02.779 --> 00:06:05.032
Uh. I'm sure of that.

160
00:06:05.115 --> 00:06:06.116
And when was it disabled?

161
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:07.159
In the morning. early?

162
00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:08.160
Or later?

163
00:06:08.243 --> 00:06:09.620
Uh. I don't know.

164
00:06:09.703 --> 00:06:11.496
When did we first open
the door on Saturday?

165
00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:12.998
Does anybody remember
what time that was?

166
00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:15.417
How can anyone remember
anything that specific?

167
00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:17.878
Hey. listen. we have to. OK?

168
00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:19.046
All right?

169
00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:20.964
Look. we have to
remember every detail.

170
00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:23.467
Mar is right. we can
make this make sense.

171
00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:26.845
Could Carrie have gotten in
during the day on Saturday?

172
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:28.597
When we were all up and
moving around and not noticed?

173
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:29.598
-It's possible.
-How?

174
00:06:29.681 --> 00:06:31.058
I don't know.

175
00:06:31.141 --> 00:06:32.392
Did anyone have any
contact with anyone

176
00:06:32.475 --> 00:06:35.854
else during that weekend?

177
00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:36.730
Like. how?

178
00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:39.858
Like. did anyone visit?

179
00:06:39.941 --> 00:06:42.402
No. no. I'm sure that
didn't happen. I'm sure...

180
00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:44.071
What?

181
00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:47.991
Just making sure you
answer Mar's question.

182
00:06:48.074 --> 00:06:49.242
About what?

183
00:06:49.325 --> 00:06:51.036
No one visited me.

184
00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:52.120
OK.

185
00:06:54.622 --> 00:06:55.958
What's that supposed to mean?

186
00:06:56.041 --> 00:06:56.917
Just let it go.

187
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.585
How did this become my fault?

188
00:06:58.668 --> 00:07:00.712
OK. hey. hey.
she hasn't done anything.

189
00:07:00.795 --> 00:07:02.422
Yeah. I didn't say she did...

190
00:07:02.505 --> 00:07:04.985
Peter. if you want to ask her
a question. just ask her. yeah?

191
00:07:11.097 --> 00:07:13.725
All right.

192
00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:15.227
You had just gotten
out of rehab.

193
00:07:15.310 --> 00:07:16.895
There it is.

194
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:18.313
And. uh. it wouldn't be the
first time you had relapsed.

195
00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:19.690
Right. Lia?

196
00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:21.566
So. maybe you had
some sketchy felon

197
00:07:21.649 --> 00:07:23.068
show up with a bunch of pills.

198
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:24.486
Because that would be.
you know. a name that we

199
00:07:24.569 --> 00:07:25.988
could give to the police.

200
00:07:26.071 --> 00:07:28.740
That... that's a lead
toward finding my son.

201
00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:30.784
That didn't happen at all.

202
00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:31.576
OK?

203
00:07:31.659 --> 00:07:34.246
No. I swear.

204
00:07:34.329 --> 00:07:36.248
And I would tell you.

205
00:07:36.331 --> 00:07:38.792
OK.

206
00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:42.087
Hey. why'd you do that?

207
00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:43.589
Do what?

208
00:07:43.672 --> 00:07:45.090
Look at her like she's
done something wrong.

209
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:46.174
She hasn't.

210
00:07:48.343 --> 00:07:49.761
What's going on? What?

211
00:07:49.844 --> 00:07:51.179
-Hey. Colin...
-Is there a problem. Colin?

212
00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:52.264
-Just let it go.
-What's going on?

213
00:07:52.347 --> 00:07:54.349
OK? Let it go.

214
00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:58.270
Anyway. why would a drug
dealer steal a stuffed frog?

215
00:07:58.353 --> 00:07:59.688
It makes no sense.

216
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:01.607
Uh. I think it makes
sense if it starts

217
00:08:01.690 --> 00:08:03.525
with my sister.
the queen of relapse.

218
00:08:03.608 --> 00:08:05.068
getting a delivery
that weekend...

219
00:08:05.151 --> 00:08:06.695
Two times!

220
00:08:06.778 --> 00:08:08.113
And Carrie being with
whoever came up there.

221
00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:11.074
And seeing Milo and her
being mentally unwell

222
00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:13.160
and forming some kind
of fucked-up obsession

223
00:08:13.243 --> 00:08:14.202
and stealing the toy.

224
00:08:14.285 --> 00:08:15.537
I think that makes sense.

225
00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:16.997
And you know what
else makes sense?

226
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:18.123
Is that my sister would
keep this from me.

227
00:08:18.206 --> 00:08:19.207
Even now.

228
00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:20.667
I wouldn't do that!

229
00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.711
I would love to be
able to believe that.

230
00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.588
There's an answer to
what happened that weekend.

231
00:08:24.671 --> 00:08:26.006
And we will figure it out.

232
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:29.051
But I cannot do
the fighting. OK?

233
00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:31.553
Not right now.

234
00:08:31.636 --> 00:08:33.472
We've gotta keep it
together for tonight.

235
00:08:33.555 --> 00:08:34.556
For Milo's sake.

236
00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:35.933
W... what's tonight?

237
00:08:36.016 --> 00:08:37.559
Hold on. are we
still doing that?

238
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.144
-Yeah.
-Doing what?

239
00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:40.687
They're coming at 8:00.

240
00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:42.189
"Real Insight's" coming
to interview them.

241
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:44.024
Yeah. the host is
flying in from LA.

242
00:08:44.107 --> 00:08:47.945
and they want to interview
them today. because it's...

243
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:49.154
Yeah.

244
00:08:49.237 --> 00:08:51.490
How does everyone know
about this but me?

245
00:08:51.573 --> 00:08:54.451
[phone chimes]

246
00:08:54.534 --> 00:08:57.204
What is it?

247
00:08:57.287 --> 00:08:58.246
Peter. what's...

248
00:08:58.329 --> 00:08:59.748
It's nothing.

249
00:08:59.831 --> 00:09:02.918
It's nothing. just. uh...
just give me a second.

250
00:09:03.001 --> 00:09:05.379
Who watches "Real Insight"?

251
00:09:05.462 --> 00:09:07.047
America. in big numbers.

252
00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:08.340
Really?

253
00:09:08.423 --> 00:09:09.841
And we need all those
people on our side.

254
00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:11.468
You're such a snob.

255
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:12.511
I'm not a snob.

256
00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:14.263
I just don't do reality TV.

257
00:09:14.346 --> 00:09:15.347
It's not reality TV.

258
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:16.431
It's a news program.

259
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:18.267
You don't "do" reality TV?

260
00:09:18.350 --> 00:09:19.601
Oh. my god.

261
00:09:19.684 --> 00:09:21.186
You're the biggest snob I know.

262
00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:22.938
