379
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:46.720
<i>[soft music]</i>

380
00:14:46.803 --> 00:14:48.138
<i>♪♪</i>

381
00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:51.892
You're right.

382
00:14:51.975 --> 00:14:54.311
I told Marissa that I would
come over before I asked you.

383
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.480
and that wasn't fair.

384
00:14:56.563 --> 00:15:00.275
Saturdays are usually your
day to do your own thing.

385
00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:08.492
Marriages are work.
and they take effort.

386
00:15:08.575 --> 00:15:10.577
And I'm gonna try
harder from now on.

387
00:15:13.288 --> 00:15:15.374
<i>Yeah. OK.</i>

388
00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:16.457
<i>Me too.</i>

389
00:15:19.294 --> 00:15:20.879
I love you.

390
00:15:20.962 --> 00:15:22.130
<i>I love you too.</i>

391
00:15:27.218 --> 00:15:29.429
[exhales]

392
00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:34.559
<i>Are you alone?</i>

393
00:15:34.642 --> 00:15:35.642
Yeah.

394
00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:39.731
Peter's out running an errand.

395
00:15:39.814 --> 00:15:41.525
And he's had to go to
a couple of stores.

396
00:15:41.608 --> 00:15:43.402
And. uh. Brian's in his studio.

397
00:15:43.485 --> 00:15:45.070
Colin and Lia. they left. I
don't know where they went.

398
00:15:45.153 --> 00:15:46.196
And I don't fucking care.

399
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:49.491
How about I make some tea?

400
00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:50.492
Yeah.

401
00:15:50.575 --> 00:15:51.535
Yes.

402
00:15:51.618 --> 00:15:52.703
Thank you.

403
00:15:52.786 --> 00:15:56.665
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

404
00:15:56.748 --> 00:16:03.672
<i>♪♪</i>

405
00:16:10.512 --> 00:16:14.725
Uh. I have to tell
you something about...

406
00:16:14.808 --> 00:16:17.060
