491
00:20:21.054 --> 00:20:27.977
<i>♪♪</i>

492
00:20:31.106 --> 00:20:33.483
[exhales]

493
00:20:33.566 --> 00:20:40.699
<i>♪♪</i>

494
00:20:49.457 --> 00:20:52.377
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

495
00:20:52.460 --> 00:20:59.592
<i>♪♪</i>

496
00:21:00.135 --> 00:21:02.804
Hi.

497
00:21:02.887 --> 00:21:03.847
Hi.

498
00:21:03.930 --> 00:21:06.600
Um. Marissa asked
me to come over.

499
00:21:06.683 --> 00:21:10.228
She... she wanted me to...

500
00:21:10.311 --> 00:21:14.942
OK. uh. I thought
it was just one stain.

501
00:21:15.025 --> 00:21:18.570
I... I think she just thought
we could do the whole thing.

502
00:21:21.322 --> 00:21:22.574
Why?

503
00:21:22.657 --> 00:21:25.410
It's something to do.

504
00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:28.830
Sitting still can be hard.

505
00:21:28.913 --> 00:21:31.333
Yeah. I think that's just
gonna exhaust her more. though.

506
00:21:31.416 --> 00:21:34.127
I mean. she hasn't really
slept in the last few days.

507
00:21:34.210 --> 00:21:36.338
Yeah. I know.

508
00:21:36.421 --> 00:21:38.632
Yeah. like. I just...

509
00:21:38.715 --> 00:21:40.717
all I'm trying to do is
help my wife. you know?

510
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:42.594
That's all I care about.

511
00:21:42.677 --> 00:21:44.262
She's really lucky to have that.

512
00:21:49.517 --> 00:21:52.062
I'm really sorry.

513
00:21:52.145 --> 00:21:54.106
Marissa told me about
everything that you've

514
00:21:54.189 --> 00:21:55.440
learned with Carrie.

515
00:21:55.523 --> 00:21:56.441
Yeah.

516
00:21:56.524 --> 00:21:59.695
But I hired her.

517
00:21:59.778 --> 00:22:03.657
And if I hadn't. then...

518
00:22:03.740 --> 00:22:05.701
I've apologized
to Marissa 100 times.

519
00:22:05.784 --> 00:22:07.494
but I've never said it to you.

520
00:22:07.577 --> 00:22:09.871
So. um. I'm really sorry.

521
00:22:14.084 --> 00:22:20.298
If Milo comes back.
he's not going to be the same.

522
00:22:23.093 --> 00:22:26.721
I don't know if Marissa and
I will recover from this.

523
00:22:29.557 --> 00:22:32.227
So I'm trying to forgive you.

524
00:22:32.310 --> 00:22:36.815
And I want you to know that.

525
00:22:36.898 --> 00:22:39.317
But I'm not there yet.

526
00:22:42.278 --> 00:22:44.030
I understand.

527
00:22:46.700 --> 00:22:50.245
Can you let me take
care of her today?

528
00:22:50.328 --> 00:22:53.999
Please. can you give me that?

529
00:22:54.082 --> 00:22:56.084
Yeah.

530
00:22:56.167 --> 00:22:59.171
Thanks.

531
00:22:59.254 --> 00:23:02.174
<i>[gentle music]</i>

532
00:23:02.257 --> 00:23:09.180
<i>♪♪</i>

533
00:23:18.273 --> 00:23:20.734
[door shuts]

534
00:23:20.817 --> 00:23:24.321
<i>♪♪</i>

535
00:23:24.404 --> 00:23:27.282
Where's Jenny?

536
00:23:27.365 --> 00:23:29.034
I told her she can go home.

537
00:23:29.117 --> 00:23:30.744
I got all the cleaning stuff.

538
00:23:30.827 --> 00:23:31.787
I'll clean the couch.

539
00:23:31.870 --> 00:23:33.372
We'll do the whole thing.

540
00:23:33.455 --> 00:23:38.085
You can go lay down.

541
00:23:38.168 --> 00:23:40.712
What?

542
00:23:40.795 --> 00:23:44.174
That wasn't your
decision to make. Peter.

543
00:23:44.257 --> 00:23:46.343
I will do the
whole couch for you.

544
00:23:46.426 --> 00:23:47.719
I wanted Jenny here.

545
00:23:47.802 --> 00:23:49.805
And I wanted to clean the couch.

546
00:23:49.888 --> 00:23:51.098
-Why?
-Why?

547
00:23:51.181 --> 00:23:52.349
Because I wanted
Jenny here. and I

548
00:23:52.432 --> 00:23:53.934
wanted to clean the couch.

549
00:23:54.017 --> 00:23:55.269
Literally. all I'm doing
is trying to help you.

550
00:23:55.352 --> 00:23:56.895
I don't know what's
going on here.

551
00:23:56.978 --> 00:23:58.563
You used to love it
when I took care of you.

552
00:23:58.646 --> 00:23:59.648
When we first met you used...

553
00:23:59.731 --> 00:24:00.649
Oh!

554
00:24:00.732 --> 00:24:02.025
I was 26.

555
00:24:02.108 --> 00:24:03.818
What is that supposed to mean?

556
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:09.533
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

557
00:24:09.616 --> 00:24:12.828
<i>♪♪</i>

558
00:24:12.911 --> 00:24:16.707
What's your favorite
thing about Milo?

559
00:24:16.790 --> 00:24:18.083
What?

560
00:24:18.166 --> 00:24:19.376
It's one of the
interview questions.

561
00:24:19.459 --> 00:24:20.335
what's your favorite thing?

562
00:24:20.418 --> 00:24:22.379
Oh. fuck.

563
00:24:22.462 --> 00:24:23.630
I haven't looked at the sheet.

564
00:24:23.713 --> 00:24:24.881
Um.

565
00:24:32.597 --> 00:24:37.561
I love when he has a nightmare
and I come into the room

566
00:24:37.644 --> 00:24:40.647
and I hold his hand
and I talk to him

567
00:24:40.730 --> 00:24:43.274
until he falls back asleep.

568
00:24:45.652 --> 00:24:48.029
I love that.

569
00:24:51.574 --> 00:24:54.453
<i>[gentle music]</i>

570
00:24:54.536 --> 00:25:01.710
<i>♪♪</i>

571
00:25:06.506 --> 00:25:08.675
[door thuds. bottles clanking]

572
00:25:08.758 --> 00:25:12.763
How do you not have...

573
00:25:12.846 --> 00:25:14.306
there's no actual
food in here. Brian.

574
00:25:14.389 --> 00:25:15.891
Which isn't a problem.
because like I said.

575
00:25:15.974 --> 00:25:17.184
I'm not really hungry.

576
00:25:17.267 --> 00:25:18.852
But you haven't eaten yet. OK?

577
00:25:18.935 --> 00:25:21.313
I'm gonna... let me...

578
00:25:21.396 --> 00:25:23.023
I'm gonna fix something
for you. and then

579
00:25:23.106 --> 00:25:24.942
I'm gonna put in a
grocery order. a real one.

580
00:25:25.025 --> 00:25:29.863
Because this shit cannot be...

581
00:25:29.946 --> 00:25:30.948
are you 12?

582
00:25:31.031 --> 00:25:32.491
They're good.

583
00:25:32.574 --> 00:25:33.742
Yeah. but they're
not... it's not real food.

584
00:25:33.825 --> 00:25:35.202
You're not a kid anymore.

585
00:25:35.285 --> 00:25:36.828
You gotta learn to
eat like an adult. OK?

586
00:25:36.911 --> 00:25:38.455
Sit. please.

587
00:25:38.538 --> 00:25:41.625
What do we got behind
door number three?

588
00:25:41.708 --> 00:25:43.126
Soup. that's a start.

589
00:25:46.796 --> 00:25:48.131
There's no soy in it.

590
00:25:48.214 --> 00:25:49.925
How do you know that for sure?

591
00:25:50.008 --> 00:25:52.010
Because I only buy
stuff you can eat. too.

592
00:25:54.387 --> 00:25:55.388
Hmm.

593
00:26:11.988 --> 00:26:13.824
Are you taking your pain meds?

594
00:26:13.907 --> 00:26:15.492
Not today.

595
00:26:15.575 --> 00:26:17.244
Because I hate them.

596
00:26:17.327 --> 00:26:18.620
You would too.

597
00:26:18.703 --> 00:26:21.123
They suck.

598
00:26:21.206 --> 00:26:24.126
We're gonna find a solution. OK?

599
00:26:24.209 --> 00:26:26.795
I could just use the chair.

600
00:26:26.878 --> 00:26:27.879
No.

601
00:26:27.962 --> 00:26:29.256
No way.

602
00:26:29.339 --> 00:26:30.591
You're not gonna be
confined to that thing.

603
00:26:30.674 --> 00:26:31.967
Not on my watch. all right?

604
00:26:32.050 --> 00:26:32.926
We can do better.

605
00:26:33.009 --> 00:26:35.970
[laughs]

606
00:26:40.517 --> 00:26:43.895
What do you think a
five-year-old remembers?

607
00:26:43.978 --> 00:26:47.608
Like. what will
Milo remember when...

608
00:26:47.691 --> 00:26:48.650
I guess. if he...

609
00:26:48.733 --> 00:26:50.944
He'll come home.

610
00:26:51.027 --> 00:26:51.945
I don't know though.

611
00:26:52.028 --> 00:26:53.780
Five is young.

612
00:26:53.863 --> 00:26:58.535
Like. I only have
little flickers

613
00:26:58.618 --> 00:27:00.162
of memories from that age.

614
00:27:00.245 --> 00:27:05.792
Like. I remember random shit
like getting out of a car

615
00:27:05.875 --> 00:27:07.169
in our home on Foxtail.

616
00:27:07.252 --> 00:27:08.170
Yeah.

617
00:27:08.253 --> 00:27:09.838
It's such a whatever memory.

618
00:27:09.921 --> 00:27:11.548
Just getting out of the car.
running up to the front door.

619
00:27:11.631 --> 00:27:14.134
I don't even remember
why I was in a hurry.

620
00:27:14.217 --> 00:27:17.262
But. you know. it must have
been before the accident.

621
00:27:17.345 --> 00:27:19.765
Sure as shit not running now.

622
00:27:19.848 --> 00:27:21.016
Yeah.

623
00:27:24.060 --> 00:27:28.273
You must've been so
scared when I got hurt.

624
00:27:28.356 --> 00:27:30.233
Sorry.

625
00:27:30.316 --> 00:27:31.526
No.

626
00:27:31.609 --> 00:27:34.863
I haven't even really
thought about it before.

627
00:27:34.946 --> 00:27:37.491
You were just a kid.

628
00:27:37.574 --> 00:27:42.120
Well. I wasn't scared.
you know. at first because I

629
00:27:42.203 --> 00:27:45.624
didn't realize it was serious.

630
00:27:45.707 --> 00:27:49.836
Um. because we were just
having so much fun. you know?

631
00:27:49.919 --> 00:27:51.797
You always played with us.

632
00:27:51.880 --> 00:27:53.090
Yeah. of course.

633
00:27:53.173 --> 00:27:54.049
Oh. my god.
you guys were a blast.

634
00:27:54.132 --> 00:27:55.384
It was...
-[laughs]

635
00:27:55.467 --> 00:27:57.094
It was the best.

636
00:27:57.177 --> 00:28:01.682
Um. yeah. I remember
Lia chasing you.

637
00:28:01.765 --> 00:28:05.018
and. uh. and she was so hyper.

638
00:28:05.101 --> 00:28:07.688
I remember her screaming.

639
00:28:07.771 --> 00:28:10.107
Yeah.

640
00:28:10.190 --> 00:28:13.277
And. uh... and I
was in the kitchen.

641
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:17.364
And she's just chasing
you around that corner.

642
00:28:17.447 --> 00:28:20.075
I was looking back at
her over my shoulder.

643
00:28:20.158 --> 00:28:23.078
Couldn't see where I was going.

644
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:25.497
You know how often I get
asked how this happened?

645
00:28:25.580 --> 00:28:27.791
I'd give anything to
have a sexier answer than

646
00:28:27.874 --> 00:28:30.460
"tripped over my own feet."

647
00:28:30.543 --> 00:28:31.503
Yeah.

648
00:28:31.586 --> 00:28:32.586
It's pathetic.

649
00:28:34.798 --> 00:28:37.384
It's the truth.

650
00:28:37.467 --> 00:28:40.554
You got there before
mom. didn't you?

651
00:28:40.637 --> 00:28:42.931
Yeah.

652
00:28:43.014 --> 00:28:46.476
I came in from the kitchen.

653
00:28:46.559 --> 00:28:49.146
And you were laying
on the pillow fort.

654
00:28:49.229 --> 00:28:52.733
But you had your eyes closed
and you weren't moving.

655
00:28:52.816 --> 00:28:58.363
so I thought you were
faking it for attention.

656
00:28:59.739 --> 00:29:03.744
Lia ran off crying to Mom.
"I didn't mean to do it.

657
00:29:03.827 --> 00:29:04.745
Don't be mad."

658
00:29:04.828 --> 00:29:05.996
[laughs]

659
00:29:06.079 --> 00:29:09.666
And. uh. so I went over to you.

660
00:29:12.252 --> 00:29:15.130
But you still
weren't getting up.

661
00:29:18.299 --> 00:29:21.261
So. I tickled you.

662
00:29:21.344 --> 00:29:24.932
Um. but you didn't move.

663
00:29:25.015 --> 00:29:27.893
<i>[somber music]</i>

664
00:29:27.976 --> 00:29:32.105
<i>♪♪</i>

665
00:29:32.188 --> 00:29:36.151
So that's when I got scared.

666
00:29:36.234 --> 00:29:37.986
<i>♪♪</i>

667
00:29:38.069 --> 00:29:39.613
Because I realized
something happened.

668
00:29:39.696 --> 00:29:42.783
You know. you must've
hit something before you

669
00:29:42.866 --> 00:29:46.161
landed on the pillows.

670
00:29:46.244 --> 00:29:47.621
You know.
then I sat there with you.

671
00:29:47.704 --> 00:29:50.165
It was just you
and me alone for what...

672
00:29:50.248 --> 00:29:54.419
what felt like
a long. long time.

673
00:29:54.502 --> 00:29:58.173
And I kept thinking that
you might not wake up.

674
00:29:58.256 --> 00:30:05.597
<i>♪♪</i>

675
00:30:06.389 --> 00:30:07.933
I'd switch with you
if I could. Brian.

676
00:30:08.016 --> 00:30:09.643
And I hate that I can't.

677
00:30:09.726 --> 00:30:16.525
<i>♪♪</i>

678
00:30:16.608 --> 00:30:20.195
[clears throat]

679
00:30:20.278 --> 00:30:22.239
Please. let me get
your pain meds.

680
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:24.032
I don't want to get tired.

681
00:30:24.115 --> 00:30:25.033
You can lay down.

682
00:30:25.116 --> 00:30:26.618
All right?

683
00:30:26.701 --> 00:30:29.788
I'll be here.

684
00:30:29.871 --> 00:30:31.039
Sure.

685
00:30:31.122 --> 00:30:32.124
I just got a refill.

686
00:30:32.207 --> 00:30:33.584
It should be in the cabinet.

687
00:30:33.667 --> 00:30:35.627
OK.

688
00:30:35.710 --> 00:30:41.049
<i>♪♪</i>

689
00:30:41.132 --> 00:30:43.093
You said you just got a refill?

690
00:30:43.176 --> 00:30:44.344
Yeah.

691
00:30:44.427 --> 00:30:45.679
Who picked it up for you?

692
00:30:45.762 --> 00:30:46.680
Lia.

693
00:30:46.763 --> 00:30:50.017
Why?

694
00:30:50.100 --> 00:30:51.018
Just curious.

695
00:30:51.101 --> 00:30:54.854
<i>[tense music]</i>

696
00:31:09.285 --> 00:31:11.830
[sighs]

697
00:31:20.171 --> 00:31:23.091
<i>[gentle music]</i>

698
00:31:23.174 --> 00:31:25.052
<i>♪♪</i>

699
00:31:25.135 --> 00:31:28.680
[blow dryer whirring]

700
00:31:31.266 --> 00:31:33.810
Hey. Mar!

701
00:31:33.893 --> 00:31:37.314
Hey. uh. I was
hoping we could. uh...

702
00:31:37.397 --> 00:31:39.983
we could talk.

703
00:31:40.066 --> 00:31:41.610
Yeah. same.

704
00:31:41.693 --> 00:31:44.154
Hey. that. uh.
Easter weekend. you...

705
00:31:44.237 --> 00:31:47.240
you went to the
art gallery. right?

706
00:31:47.323 --> 00:31:48.951
Why does that matter?

707
00:31:49.034 --> 00:31:51.787
I'm just trying to
remember all the details.

708
00:31:51.870 --> 00:31:52.996
Peter went to get juice.

709
00:31:53.079 --> 00:31:54.623
I was putting Milo to sleep.

710
00:31:54.706 --> 00:32:00.796
And you. Brian. and Lia.
you went to the art gallery?

711
00:32:00.879 --> 00:32:02.130
Right.

712
00:32:02.213 --> 00:32:04.174
The three of you?

713
00:32:04.257 --> 00:32:05.676
Yeah. the three of us.

714
00:32:05.759 --> 00:32:07.928
Looking at art?

715
00:32:08.011 --> 00:32:11.306
It was a friend of Lia's.

716
00:32:11.389 --> 00:32:13.516
She wanted to show
support. I guess.

717
00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:19.147
Yeah. I didn't think you'd
lie to me a third time.

718
00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:20.357
Obviously. I was wrong.

719
00:32:20.440 --> 00:32:22.859
Hey. listen. I can explain. OK?

720
00:32:22.942 --> 00:32:23.860
I've spoken to Brian.

721
00:32:23.943 --> 00:32:25.236
Where were you and Lia?

722
00:32:27.781 --> 00:32:30.534
You do not honestly
believe that we had something

723
00:32:30.617 --> 00:32:32.244
to do with Milo's kidnapping.

724
00:32:32.327 --> 00:32:34.371
I think that Carrie Finch
got into our lives somehow.

725
00:32:34.454 --> 00:32:35.539
And you're hiding
something from me.

726
00:32:35.622 --> 00:32:37.124
And I don't know what that is.

727
00:32:37.207 --> 00:32:38.500
OK. look. look.
Lia and I have been

728
00:32:38.583 --> 00:32:41.587
seeing each other for months.

729
00:32:41.670 --> 00:32:44.715
And. Brian. he had something
that he wanted to do.

730
00:32:44.798 --> 00:32:47.009
We dropped him off for a bit.
and then we went to dinner.

731
00:32:47.092 --> 00:32:48.969
It doesn't get any more
exciting than that.

732
00:32:49.052 --> 00:32:50.429
OK?

733
00:32:50.512 --> 00:32:52.055
And I am sure that I
could find the charge

734
00:32:52.138 --> 00:32:54.016
on my credit card statement
if you need to see it.

735
00:32:54.099 --> 00:32:56.560
You're dating my sister?

736
00:32:56.643 --> 00:32:57.644
Shit.

737
00:32:57.727 --> 00:32:58.979
Shit.

738
00:32:59.062 --> 00:33:00.271
Um.

739
00:33:02.982 --> 00:33:04.359
Yeah.

740
00:33:04.442 --> 00:33:09.031
And I know that it
might be weird that I

741
00:33:09.114 --> 00:33:10.574
am involved with your sister.

742
00:33:10.657 --> 00:33:12.868
Uh. no. no. I don't...

743
00:33:12.951 --> 00:33:14.036
I don't care about that.

744
00:33:14.119 --> 00:33:15.370
I'm not a Neanderthal.

745
00:33:15.453 --> 00:33:16.622
And my sister's an adult.
She can...

746
00:33:16.705 --> 00:33:18.999
she can date who she wants.

747
00:33:19.082 --> 00:33:24.046
I do care that you're
both addicts. though.

748
00:33:24.129 --> 00:33:27.215
OK. we're... we're not the
same kind of addict. Peter.

749
00:33:27.298 --> 00:33:28.884
Fine. yeah.

750
00:33:28.967 --> 00:33:30.761
No. you're a gambling
addict. and she likes pills.

751
00:33:30.844 --> 00:33:33.388
But you're not really supposed
to date each other. right?

752
00:33:33.471 --> 00:33:36.683
No. it's...
it's not like a rule.

753
00:33:36.766 --> 00:33:41.855
No. but it's not
exactly encouraged. is it?

754
00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:44.066
-No.
-No.

755
00:33:44.149 --> 00:33:46.944
Because it puts you both
at a risk for relapse.

756
00:33:47.027 --> 00:33:48.320
I... I trusted you.

757
00:33:48.403 --> 00:33:50.072
I... I... I went into
business with you.

758
00:33:50.155 --> 00:33:51.573
And I put my name next
to yours on a wall.

759
00:33:51.656 --> 00:33:52.908
because I trusted you. Colin.

760
00:33:52.991 --> 00:33:54.076
Listen. my personal
life has nothing

761
00:33:54.159 --> 00:33:55.118
to do with our business.

762
00:33:55.201 --> 00:33:56.536
I would never put that at risk.

763
00:33:56.619 --> 00:33:57.996
Well. well. it has in the past.

764
00:33:58.079 --> 00:33:59.581
I mean. are you...
are you gambling again?

765
00:33:59.664 --> 00:34:01.249
No.
He's not the one who relapsed.

766
00:34:01.332 --> 00:34:02.709
Lia is.

767
00:34:02.792 --> 00:34:04.670
Brian's pills are missing.

768
00:34:04.753 --> 00:34:05.671
What?

769
00:34:05.754 --> 00:34:06.505
Yeah.

770
00:34:06.588 --> 00:34:08.090
No. listen. hey.

771
00:34:08.173 --> 00:34:09.299
Lia did not take those...

772
00:34:09.382 --> 00:34:10.759
How the fuck would you know?

773
00:34:10.842 --> 00:34:11.802
-Lia did not take those pills.
-Right. no.

774
00:34:11.885 --> 00:34:12.928
What?

775
00:34:13.011 --> 00:34:14.888
They just got up and
left on their own?

776
00:34:14.971 --> 00:34:16.515
I don't know.
Maybe it's a misunderstanding.

777
00:34:16.598 --> 00:34:17.391
Have you even asked
her if she took them?

778
00:34:17.474 --> 00:34:18.392
Why would I?

779
00:34:18.475 --> 00:34:21.644
Addicts lie.

780
00:34:23.688 --> 00:34:29.194
[laughs] Oh. come on. you...

781
00:34:29.277 --> 00:34:30.779
What?

782
00:34:30.862 --> 00:34:33.282
You kind of love
this. don't you?

783
00:34:33.365 --> 00:34:34.324
Excuse me?

784
00:34:34.407 --> 00:34:35.742
Yeah.

